mn":55,"offset":2697},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"It means the browser can download a single background image, cache it, use it in multiple places, but still be able to use multiple colors in certain situations. An example is by using media queries where you can make ","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1,"offset":2699},"end":{"line":33,"column":219,"offset":2917},"indent":[]}},{"type":"html","value":"<code class=\"language-text\">if</code>","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":219,"offset":2917},"end":{"line":33,"column":223,"offset":2921},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" statements in your CSS so that you could even have darker filters on mobile vs tablet, vs desktop if the image is placed in a different spot due to responsive design. You can use this technique to darken only the ones you need, but still only have a single image being served","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":223,"offset":2921},"end":{"line":33,"column":499,"offset":3197},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1,"offset":2699},"end":{"line":33,"column":499,"offset":3197},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Anther reason you may want this is if you are serving an image from an external site via an API, such as Facebook or Instagram. You can use this CSS as well as others to create your own image filters and even get a little crazy - all within the browser. That means you don’t have to modify the original image or do any server-side manipulation, which is great for scalability, but also ensures you conserve the original image while saving bandwidth and storage space if that’s something you need.","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1,"offset":3199},"end":{"line":35,"column":497,"offset":3695},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1,"offset":3199},"end":{"line":35,"column":497,"offset":3695},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Are there any other similar CSS tricks you’ve found to save yourself from having to edit the original image in Photoshop multiple times?","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1,"offset":3697},"end":{"line":37,"column":137,"offset":3833},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1,"offset":3697},"end":{"line":37,"column":137,"offset":3833},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1,"offset":0},"end":{"line":37,"column":137,"offset":3833}}}}